io.github.cantido.qlearner.gridworld.client

Class GridWorldEnvironment

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.github.cantido.qlearner.gridworld.client.GridWorldEnvironment
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Environment

    @NotThreadSafe
public class GridWorldEnvironment
extends Object
implements Environment
    An implementation of Q-Learning that moves an agent through a grid from a starting State to a goal State.

    To drive the Agent from start state to goal state, each state has a reward value of negative one, except for the goal state, which has a reward of 10. Once we reach the goal state, we reset the agent and let it find its way again. After enough iterations, the Agent builds up enough quality values to know the correct path to the goal state in a minimal number of moves.

        Build a GridWorldEnvironment of the specified size, with the specified starting point and goal point.
        Parameters:
        columnsCount - horizontal size of the grid, in the interval [1, Integer.MAX_VALUE]
        rowsCount - vertical size of the grid, in the interval [1, Integer.MAX_VALUE]
        startingColumnIndex - horizontal, array-indexed position of the starting state, in the interval [0, columnsCount]
        startingRowIndex - vertical, array-indexed position of the starting state, in the interval [0, rowsCount]
        goalColumnIndex - horizontal, array-indexed position of the goal state, in the interval [0, columnsCount]
        goalRowIndex - vertical, array-indexed position of the goal state, in the interval [0, rowsCount]
